      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The small quantity of fresh snow and in particular the wind slabs formed by the strong wind are lying on the unfavourable surface of an old snowpack. <br/> Individual weak layers exist in the old snowpack especially on shady slopes. Avalanches can in some places be released in deep layers in particular on northwest, north and northeast facing slopes. <br/> Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise as the day progresses to moistening of the snowpack in particular on sunny slopes."
